Our District will be taking steps to limit spectator attendance at our activities this fall. The premise of limiting attendance is based on these three goals:

o Keep all students and staff safe.
o Keep all students and staff in school as long as possible.
o Give all students the opportunity to participate in activities.

• Our District believes limiting spectator attendance provides our students the best opportunity to complete their seasons and reduces the likelihood of community transmission.

https://5il.co/jqvv

post_text:
Based on input received from our School Board at their special meeting on August 3, following is the link to our District’s Revised 20-21 Return to Learning Plan. The facial covering/mask “requirement” for students and staff has been changed to “highly recommended.” The Plan now includes a list of Activities protocols on pages 12-27 as well.

https://5il.co/j7j2

Our District’s Revised Return to Learning Plan will be given a second reading by our School Board at their regular meeting on Monday, August 10 at 5:30 p.m. in the high school library. If you would like to provide any feedback to our school board regarding the Revised Plan, community input time is scheduled for 6:30 p.m.

It would be the intent of our Board to discuss any changes and/or modifications to the plan that evening and eventually move to adopt the Return to Learning Plan prior to the start of the 20-21 school year.

Thank you for reading and reviewing our District’s Revised Return to Learning Plan.

post_text: Due to the likelihood of rain on Saturday, May 16, the BHS Class of 2020 Parade at 4:00 p.m. and Fireworks at 9:30 p.m. have been moved to Sunday, May 17 at the same times. The Virtual Graduation will stay on schedule at 2:00 p.m. on Saturday, May 16.
text: Due to the likelihood of rain on Saturday, May 16, the BHS Class of 2020 Parade at 4:00 p.m. and Fireworks at 9:30 p.m. have been moved to Sunday, May 17 at the same times. The Virtual Graduation will stay on schedule at 2:00 p.m. on Saturday, May 16.

post_text: Please support our BHS Class of 2020 by viewing their Virtual Graduation Ceremony on Saturday, May 16 at 2:00 p.m.! A link will be provided at 1:45 p.m. on our District’s webpage (www.beresford.k12.sd.us) news and social media—live feed, twitter, and Facebook. Please cheer on our graduates at 4:00 p.m. as they take part in a car parade (https://bit.ly/5-16Parade) through Beresford neighborhoods led by our local police department! At 9:30 p.m., we will honor our graduates with a fireworks display!

post_text: The BHS Alumni Album inserts for the classes of 2010-2019 are available in the district business office. Please bring in your alumni album and we will place the insert in your booklet. There is no charge as the BHS All-School Reunion Committee has paid for the updates.

post_text: Congratulations to the BHS and BMS Marching Bands on a great performance at the Parker Marching Festival on Sept. 20. Both bands placed 2nd in the Class "A" division! Please come out on Friday and watch our marching bands perform in downtown Beresford at 9:45 am and 2:00 pm!
